{"word":"νοσώδης","slug":"νοσώδης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>νοσώδης</b></el> <el>(νος-ώδης, ες) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:εἶδος'><el>εἶδος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>sickly, diseased, ailing</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>pestilential, baneful</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}